The EntityManger is the primary interface for interacting with the persistence context in Java Persistence API(JPA). When working with JPQL(Java Persistence Query Language), the EntityManger is used to create, execute and manage JPQL queries.

Steps: All these below code are written in service layer

In the service layer create an Entity Manager, to allow dependency injection

@Autowired
private EntityManager entityManager;                                     

public Optional<Student> findByEmail(String email){                             

String jpql = "select s from Student s where s.email=:mail";                        //JPQL is used here
TypedQuery<Student> query = entityManager.createQuery(jpql,Student.class);   
query.setParameter("mail",email);

Student student = query.getSingleResult();
return student;

}


